Questions:
What will happen if you choose to withdraw from the Estudio Oportunidad study?
A) You will be required to reimburse the cost of the study visits you have attended;
B) You will no longer be able to access HIV care services at SAI;
C) You may stop participating at any time and it will not affect your ability to receive free HIV care at SAI;
D) You will be obligated to participate in future unrelated studies as a condition of your withdrawal.

Correct answer: C

If you decide not to participate in the Estudio Oportunidad study, what alternative cervical cancer screening option is available to you?
A) You can receive a standard cervical screening using a mammogram; 
B) You can access a Pap smear for screening of cervical cancer through the Servicio Nacional de Salud (SNS) or with a provider of your choice;
C) There are no alternative screening options available outside of the study;
D) You will be provided with a home testing kit for cervical cancer screening.

Correct answer: B

If you experience an injury related to your participation in the Estudio Oportunidad, whom should you contact immediately for assistance?

A) Your personal physician;
B) Dr. Yeycy Donastorg or Dr. Flavia Lantigua;
C) The nearest emergency room;
D) The study financial sponsor, the US National Cancer Institute (NCI).

Correct answer: B) Dr. Yeycy Donastorg or Dr. Flavia Lantigua;
